.TH "WEBTRANSPORTRECEIVESTREAM" "3JS" "February 24, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WebTransportReceiveStream \- WebTransportReceiveStream
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[CR]WebTransportReceiveStream\f[R] interface of the WebTransport
API is a \f[CR]ReadableStream\f[R] that can be used to read from an
incoming unidirectional or bidirectional \f[CR]WebTransport\f[R] stream.
.PP
The stream is a readable byte stream of \f[CR]Uint8Array\f[R], and can
be consumed using either a BYOB reader
(\f[CR]ReadableStreamBYOBReader\f[R]) or the default reader
(\f[CR]ReadableStreamDefaultReader\f[R]).
.PP
Objects of this type are not constructed directly.
Instead they are obtained using the
\f[CR]WebTransport.incomingUnidirectionalStream\f[R] property.
.PP
\f[CR]WebTransportReceiveStream\f[R] is a transferable object.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
\f[I]Inherits properties from its parent interface,
\f[CI]ReadableStream\f[I].\f[R]
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
\f[I]Also inherits properties from its parent interface,
\f[CI]ReadableStream\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]WebTransportReceiveStream.getStats()\f[R]
Returns a \f[CR]Promise\f[R] that resolves with statistics related to
this stream.
.SH EXAMPLES
See \f[CR]WebTransport.incomingUnidirectionalStreams\f[R] for an example
of how to get a \f[CR]ReadableStream\f[R] of
\f[CR]WebTransportReceiveStream\f[R] objects.
